initial statement:
 1087
Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I acknowledge the severity of my actions and the potential consequences they could have had. I want to take this opportunity to express my remorse and acknowledge the importance of accountability.

On the day in question, I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members. Despite being fully aware of the speed limit, I made the poor decision to drive aggressively and exceeded the permitted speed. I also compounded my negligence by answering a text message while behind the wheel.

Regrettably, my reckless behavior resulted in a collision with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was injured in the incident. However, this incident serves as a stark reminder of the dangers of distracted driving and the potential harm that could have occurred.

I acknowledge that I bear full responsibility for my actions and should have prioritized the safety of myself and others on the road. It is clear that my behavior was unacceptable and I recognize the need for consequences.

In terms of my degree of involvement, I acknowledge that I was the sole driver and decision-maker in this situation. I understand that my actions played a direct role in the outcome of the incident.

I would like to bring to your attention some information about myself that may be considered mitigating factors. Firstly, I am 37 years old and have a clean record up until this incident. I believe that my past behavior demonstrates that this event was an isolated lapse in judgment rather than a pattern of dangerous driving.

Furthermore, I am actively involved in giving back to the community through regular donations to the British Heart Foundation. This demonstrates my commitment to society and my understanding of the importance of supporting charitable causes.

In conclusion, I fully accept responsibility for my actions and acknowledge the seriousness of the offense. My guilty plea demonstrates my willingness to accept the consequences of my behavior. I humbly ask for the court's leniency in sentencing, taking into consideration my clean record, my remorse, and my commitment to making amends. I assure you that I have learned my lesson and will make every effort to ensure that such recklessness will never be repeated.
NEW STATEMENT:

1190
Your Honor,

I respectfully come before the court today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I want to express my sincere remorse and accept full responsibility for my careless actions on that day. 

As I reflect upon the events that led to this unfortunate incident, I am deeply ashamed of the poor choices I made while driving to the airport to pick up my family members. I understand the gravity of my behavior - driving aggressively and exceeding the speed limit, as well as indulging in the dangerous act of texting while driving.

The consequences of my actions resulted in a collision with a guardrail. Thankfully, no other individuals were harmed in the incident, but I am acutely aware of the potential dangers my actions could have posed to other road users.

I fully acknowledge that my behavior was unacceptable and lacked consideration for the safety of myself and others. I can only imagine the anxiety and fear that I may have caused those who witnessed the aftermath of the crash.

I believe it is important to address some aspects of my character that may serve as mitigating factors. Although this incident was a grievous mistake, I naively allowed stress and urgency to cloud my judgment. Prior to this incident, I had maintained an otherwise clean driving record, exhibiting responsible and lawful behavior on the road.

Additionally, I would like to highlight my philanthropic efforts as an active contributor to the British Heart Foundation. Through regular donations, I strive to make a positive impact on the lives affected by heart disease. This commitment demonstrates my dedication to giving back to society and assisting those in need.

In concluding my statement, I want to emphasize that I wholeheartedly accept accountability for my actions. My guilty plea is an admission of my wrongdoing and an acknowledgment of the seriousness of the offense. I humbly request the court's leniency in considering my clean driving record, my genuine remorse, and my commitment to making amends.

I offer my deepest apologies to the court, to society, and especially to those who may have been affected by my reckless actions. I assure you that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience. I am committed to becoming a more responsible and conscientious driver, ensuring the safety of myself and others on the road is always paramount.

Thank you for your understanding, Your Honor.
