Your Honor,

I stand before you today to take full responsibility for the charge of careless driving. I would like to express my deepest regrets and convey my sincere remorse for my actions.

On the day of the incident, I was en route to the airport to pick up my family members. Unfortunately, due to being in a rush, I drove aggressively and exceeded the speed limit. Additionally, I made the negligent decision to answer a text message while driving.

Thankfully, no one else was injured in the accident involving the guardrail. However, I fully acknowledge the potential harm and danger I put myself and others in with my reckless behavior. It is only now, upon reflection, that I realize the gravity of my actions and the potential consequences.

I would like to assure the court that this incident serves as a wake-up call for me. I deeply regret my actions and their potential to cause harm. At 37 years old, I have maintained an otherwise clean record, and I am an active supporter of the British Heart Foundation, regularly contributing donations.

Your Honor, I humbly ask for your consideration in sentencing, as I accept full responsibility for my careless actions.

Sincerely,
Charlotte Porter

